Explanation:
The solution iterates through the digits of n using a while loop. For each digit, it divides n by 10 to remove the last digit and increments the count variable. Since the loop runs log(n) times (as we divide by 10 each time), the time complexity is O(log(n)). The solution uses a single integer variable for space complexity, which is O(1) since the space required is constant. The energy implications are low as the solution only performs arithmetic operations and does not involve any resource-intensive tasks.

